<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Contributing and Community on Documentation</title><link>/project/</link><description>Recent content in Contributing and Community on Documentation</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><lastBuildDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</lastBuildDate><atom:link href="/project/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Frequently Asked Questions</title><link>/project/faq/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/project/faq/</guid><description>&lt;h2 id="general-faqs"&gt;
	General FAQs
&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;details&gt;
 &lt;summary&gt;
 &lt;h6&gt;Question: What is Meshery?&lt;/h6&gt;
&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Answer:&lt;/strong&gt; Meshery is a self-service engineering platform that enables collaborative design and operation of cloud and cloud native infrastructure.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/details&gt;
&lt;details&gt;
 &lt;summary&gt;
 &lt;h6&gt;Question: Why was Meshery created?&lt;/h6&gt;
&lt;/summary&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Answer:&lt;/strong&gt; As an open source, vendor-neutral project, Meshery was created out of the necessity to enable platform engineers, site reliability engineers, and DevSecOps teams to collaborate in the management of their infrastructure and workloads. Meshery was created as an extensible platform to serve a broad set of modern application management needs.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Community</title><link>/project/community/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/project/community/</guid><description>&lt;p&gt;Meshery is a CNCF project maintained by engineers from NetSkope, Google, VMware, Red Hat, Rackspace, Citrix, Instabase, Layer5, Microsoft, OpenGov, Computas AS, Rill Data, Quantex, Lumina Networks, API7, F5, Citi, Acquia, HashiCorp, TCS, DigitalOcean, Solarwinds, and others. Meshery is an open source project that adheres to the &lt;a href="https://github.com/cncf/foundation/blob/master/code-of-conduct.md"&gt;CNCF&amp;rsquo;s Code of Conduct&lt;/a&gt;. Meshery advance the state of the art surrounding cloud native management and enable adopters of Cloud Native technologies and techniques to do so with confidence. Our shared commitment to the open source spirit pushes Meshery forward.&lt;/p&gt;</description></item><item><title>Meshery-Cilium Past Results</title><link>/project/compatibility-matrix/meshery-cilium-past-results/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/project/compatibility-matrix/meshery-cilium-past-results/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Meshery-Consul Past Results</title><link>/project/compatibility-matrix/meshery-consul-past-results/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/project/compatibility-matrix/meshery-consul-past-results/</guid><description/></item><item><title>Meshery-Istio Past Results</title><link>/project/compatibility-matrix/meshery-istio-past-results/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>/